\sigma_{t+1}^2=\sigma_t^2
\mu_t=\frac1n\sum_{i=1}^n{x_i}\;\;\;\;\;\sigma_t^2=\frac1n\sum_{i=1}^n{x_i^2}-\mu_t^2
\mu_{t+1} =\frac1n(x_1+1)+\frac1n\sum_{i=2}^n{x_i} =\frac1n{x_1}+\frac1n\sum_{i=2}^n{x_i}+\frac1n =\frac1n\sum_{i=1}^n{x_i}+\frac1n =\mu_t+\frac1n
\sigma_{t+1}^2 =\frac1n(x_1+1)^2+\frac1n\sum_{i=2}^n{x_i^2}-\mu_{t+1}^2 =\frac1n(x_1^2+2x_1+1)+\frac1n\sum_{i=2}^n{x_i^2}-(\mu_t+\frac1n)^2
=\frac1n(x_1^2)+\frac1n\sum_{i=2}^n{x_i^2}+\frac1n(2x_1+1)-(\mu_t^2+\frac{2\mu_t}n+\frac1{n^2})
=\frac1n\sum_{i=1}^n{x_i^2}-\mu_t^2+\frac1n(2x_1+1-2\mu_t-\frac1n)
=\sigma_t^2+\frac1n(2x_1+1-2\mu_t-\frac1n)
\sigma_{t+1}^2=\sigma_t^2+\frac1n(1-\frac1n)=\sigma_t^2+\frac1n-\frac1{n^2}
